+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NUyxzL6uQUMP8gF2pF3Esz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Architecture Summary\n\nThis is an **event-driven order processing system** designed as a hard debugging benchmark. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. Source Files (/workspace/src/)\n\n**Events Layer:**\n- `/workspace/src/events/bus.ts` - Central EventBus for pub/sub messaging\n- `/workspace/src/events/types.ts` - Event interfaces and type definitions\n\n**Orders Module:**\n- `/workspace/src/orders/service.ts` - OrderService handling creation, cancellation, refunds\n- `/workspace/src/orders/repository.ts` - In-memory order storage\n\n**Inventory Module:**\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts` - Manages stock reservation/release on events\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts` - Stock tracking with available/reserved counts\n\n**Billing Module:**\n- `/workspace/src/billing/service.ts` - Payment processing and refund handling\n- `/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts` - Order total calculation with tax and discount\n\n**Notifications Module:**\n- `/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts` - Sends order confirmations, cancellations, refunds\n\n**Main Entry:**\n- `/workspace/src/index.ts` - Exports all public APIs\n\n### 2. Test Files (/workspace/tests/)\n\n- `/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/events.test.ts`\n\n### 3. Architecture Overview\n\n**Event-Driven Flow:**\nThe system uses a central EventBus with 8 defined events:\n- `order.created` - Triggers inventory reservation\n- `order.confirmed` - Order payment confirmed\n- `order.cancelled` - Initiates stock release\n- `order.refunded` - Triggers refund notification\n- `payment.charged` - Payment processed\n- `stock.reserved` - Stock reserved successfully\n- `stock.released` - Stock released from reservation\n- `notification.sent` - Notification delivered\n\n**Key Design Patterns:**\n1. **Pub/Sub Pattern**: Services register event handlers and emit events\n2. **Repository Pattern**: Each module (Orders, Inventory) has a repository for data persistence\n3. **Service Layer**: Business logic encapsulated in service classes\n4. **Global Handler Registry**: EventBus maintains a module-level handler map shared across instances\n\n**Data Flow Example (Order Creation):**\n```\nOrderService.createOrder()\n  ↓ (emits ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED)\nInventoryService.handleOrderCreated()\n  ↓ (reserves stock, emits ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED)\nBillingService.handleStockReserved()\n  ↓ (emits ORDER_EVENTS.PAYMENT_CHARGED)\n```\n\n**Module Dependencies:**\n- OrderService → EventBus, OrderRepository, BillingService\n- InventoryService → EventBus, InventoryRepository\n- BillingService → EventBus, NotificationService\n- NotificationService (standalone)\n\n### 4. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── events/\n│   │   ├── bus.ts\n│   │   └── types.ts\n│   ├── orders/\n│   │   ├── service.ts\n│   │   └── repository.ts\n│   ├── inventory/\n│   │   ├── service.ts\n│   │   └── repository.ts\n│   ├── billing/\n│   │   ├── service.ts\n│   │   └── calculator.ts\n│   └── notifications/\n│       └── service.ts\n├── tests/ (5 test files)\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .eslintrc.cjs\n```\n\n**Total: 10 source files + 5 test files + 4 config files**"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a282c24 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 22835\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 26681</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d3440a2c-177e-4bfb-a459-c0461ee78711","uuid":"7b801e01-1af8-467d-a68a-45ab21058fb8","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace. I need to understand the full architecture of this event-driven order processing system. Please:\n1. List all source fil